he didn't even clear off his desk.

364
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:18,000
Just disappeared, off the grid.

365
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:20,640
You knew, didn't you?

366
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,200
You knew all along it was him.

367
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:24,840
That's why you came to see us
so fast.

368
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:26,680
That's incorrect.

369
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:29,240
Viper can only be produced
in a state-of-the-art lab,

370
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,280
like yours.

371
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:34,560
Stan Potolsky is a brilliant man,

372
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:37,800
perfectly capable of building
his own lab.

373
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,360
But you are more than welcome
to examine our facilities.

374
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,840
With full and proper clearances,
of course.

375
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,840
Of course.

376
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,160
We'll get the paperwork started.

377
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:52,440
Lawyers. Scumbags, the lot of them.

378
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:53,920
Yeah, some of them.

379
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,280
Let's go find Stan Potolsky.

380
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:56,800
What, drive around looking for him?

381
00:21:56,880 --> 00:22:00,360
No. I'll call dispatch,
have them put out an APB.

382
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,640
All right, I'll check with the desk,
see if his name's come up.

383
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:06,880
- Gordon, right?
