384
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:09,560
You got to come with me now,
nice and quiet like.

385
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:12,600
- What are you talking about?
- Relax. We got a mutual friend.

386
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:15,480
- Oh, yeah, who's that?
- Oswald Cobblepot.

387
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:18,040
Yeah, him.

388
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:19,760
And if you don't come with me now,

389
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:22,600
we're gonna put his head in a bag
and send it to Falcone,

390
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:25,440
which would be embarrassing for you,
no?

391
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:29,160
Or maybe we've been misinformed.

392
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:31,040
I mean, if I'm not ringing
any bells here,

393
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:32,360
you can go on your merry way.

394
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:35,680
No, I'll come.

395
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:46,480
Come on, shove over.

396
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:49,480
Hey! Hey!

397
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,360
Welcome.

398
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:06,520
I'm Salvatore Maroni.

399
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,400
I know who you are.

400
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:10,720
What do you want?

401
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,600
- Here's the thing...
- Jim, just tell the truth.

402
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:16,920
You want a drink, Jim?

403
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:19,920
I'm having a Negroni.
So good with seafood.

404
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:22,280
Water.

405
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:30,280
So, our friend here told me
a fascinating story.

406
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:31,360
Never heard a story so good.

407
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:33,240
It's hard to believe it's true.

408
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:35,800
